  "translations": {
    "en": {
      "description": {
        "text": "A fine sport climbing crag right on the shore of Lake Mälaren. (Bring your swimming gear!) Mostly bolted routes and a real mecca for climbers operating in the 6c–7b range. Well protected.",
        "method": "llm",
        "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
        "sourceIds": [
          "legacy:gaseborg"
        ]
      },
      "sections": {
        "allmant": {
          "title": {
            "text": "General",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:gaseborg"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "A fine sport crag right on the shore of Lake Mälaren. (Bring your swimming gear!) Mostly bolted routes and a real mecca for anyone climbing in the 6c–7b range. Well protected.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:gaseborg"
            ]
          }
        },
        "vagbeskrivning": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Directions",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:gaseborg"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "Take the E18 towards Oslo. Turn off towards Viksjö. Follow Viksjöleden and turn left onto Hummelmoravägen. Turn left onto Basunvägen and park in the visitors’ car park. (A Google map is available on a separate page.) Follow the cycle path towards the woods and pass the barrier. Follow the path and cross the floodlit trail twice. The path crosses a footbridge and forks 120 metres beyond it. Take the left fork—the path is marked with yellow triangles. Cross the gravel road and follow the yellow triangles/orange trail markers. After about 5 minutes you reach another road and a tree marked with a yellow triangle and an arrow pointing left, as well as an orange marker and an arrow pointing right—turn right and follow the orange markers. After about 20 metres, turn left onto another path.\n\nYou are now at the ancient hillfort. Keep right to enter the hillfort; keep left to descend to Ravinen.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:gaseborg"
            ]
          }
        },
        "klippor": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Crags",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:gaseborg"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "Gåseborg is easy to navigate. Ravinen is the first sector you reach if you keep left at the ancient hillfort. You can then follow the water while maintaining some height, which brings you up roughly by Gula Väggen. Djävulsväggen is then about 75 metres north/to the left, and Ovanför Ravinen around 20 metres south/to the right. From Ovanför Ravinen, head towards the water to reach a firepit directly above Ravinen’s top anchors. If you prefer to go straight to Djävulsväggen for a warm-up, keep right at the ancient hillfort.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:gaseborg"
            ]
          }
        },
        "ravinen": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Ravinen",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:gaseborg"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "The first part of the routes is slightly overhanging, after which the wall becomes a steep slab. Several anchors can be reached from above.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:gaseborg"
            ]
          }
        },
        "ovanfor-ravinen": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Ovanför Ravinen",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:gaseborg"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "The crag, called “Överhängande väggen” in the latest Stockholm guidebook (1996!), previously had three reported routes, as well as signs of earlier activity. There are now also several fine sport routes with bolts and lower-off anchors. One way to reach it is to walk straight past the firepit inside the ancient hillfort, following a small path which, after a little scrambling, leads directly to the wall. Anyone wishing to reach the anchors from above can, with the utmost caution, climb down via the hillfort on top of the crag. Abseil the final section; the ground is loose at the crag edge... The steep section is around 10 m high.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:gaseborg"
            ]
          }
        },
        "gula-vaggen": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Gula Väggen",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:gaseborg"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "20 m to the left of Ovanför Ravinen",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:gaseborg"
            ]
          }
        },
        "djavulsvaggen": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Djävulsväggen",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:gaseborg"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "There are no top anchors, but two substantial pine trees make up for this.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:gaseborg"
            ]
          }
        }
      },
      "routes": {
        "gaseborg-led-1": {
          "description": {
            "text": "New route left of Vickevire, sharing the same anchor. Well bolted, mostly on large holds, with some laybacking if desired.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:gaseborg"
            ]
          }
        },
        "gaseborg-led-2": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Finally climbable, now equipped with hangers and a couple of new bolts.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:gaseborg"
            ]
          }
        },
        "gaseborg-led-3": {
          "description": {
            "text": "The first bolt has now been replaced (Bultkommittén, Oct -11).",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:gaseborg"
            ]
          }
        },
        "gaseborg-led-4": {
          "description": {
            "text": "New anchor and a new bolt at the start (Bultkommittén, Oct -11).",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:gaseborg"
            ]
          }
        },
        "gaseborg-led-5": {
          "description": {
            "text": "New bolt at the start (Bultkommittén, Oct -11).",
