        "gaseborg-led-55": {
          "description": {
            "text": "The route starts by an inscription carved into the rock, “Till minne av...”, about one metre left of the start of Wall Hall. It continues up the slab/face about 1–1.5 m left of Wall Hall all the way, without touching it, to the pine. Moving out to the edge a couple of metres to the left makes the route considerably easier. The route eases after the crux above the second bolt, but remains high-quality climbing all the way to the top. A slightly straighter, finer line than Wall Hall and considerably more demanding on both feet and fingers.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
